This HTML file creates a basic ToDoList app:

- **Header:** Displays the logo and title.
- **Input Section:** Allows users to add new tasks.
- **Filter Buttons:** Lets users filter tasks by status (All, Completed, Pending).
- **Task List:** Shows added tasks in a list format.
- **Footer:** Contains a copyright notice.

HERE BELOW THE CODE ----------------------------------------------------

<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8">
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
  <title>ToDoList</title>
  <link rel="stylesheet" href="ToDoList.css">
</head>
<body>
  <div class="container">

<!-------------->
<div class="header">
  <img src="icon.jpg" alt="Logo" class="Logo" height="40" width="40"/>
  <h1>TO-DO-LIST</h1>
</div>

<!-------------------->
<div class="Input-container"></div>
<input type="text" id="taskInput" placeholder="Enter your task here"/>
<button onclick="addTask()">Add Task</button>

<!-------------->
<div class="filter-container">
  <button onclick="filterTask('all')">All Tasks</button>
  <button onclick="filterTask('Completed')">Completed Tasks</button>
  <button onclick="filterTask('Pending')">Pending Tasks</button>
</div>


<!---------------->
<ul id="taskList"></ul>

<!---------------------->
<div class="footer">
  <p>&copy; 2024 PreetiFartyal. All rights reserved</p>
</div>
  </div>
  <script src="ToDoList.js"></script>
</body>
</html>
